&lt;p data-start=&quot;0&quot; data-end=&quot;55&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full-Stack Software Engineer (Application Software)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;0&quot; data-end=&quot;55&quot;&gt;Compensation: Level 1: $108,000–$138,000 | Level 2: $126,000–$154,000 + equity&lt;br data-start=&quot;130&quot; data-end=&quot;133&quot;&gt;Location: El Segundo, CA&lt;br data-start=&quot;157&quot; data-end=&quot;160&quot;&gt;Work Policy: Onsite&lt;br data-start=&quot;179&quot; data-end=&quot;182&quot;&gt;Level: L1–L2&lt;br data-start=&quot;194&quot; data-end=&quot;197&quot;&gt;Hiring Count: 1&lt;br data-start=&quot;212&quot; data-end=&quot;215&quot;&gt;Core KPIs: FactoryOS development, production workflow digitization, equipment/data integrations, application reliability, and practical software adoption by manufacturing and operations teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;57&quot; data-end=&quot;73&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;75&quot; data-end=&quot;471&quot;&gt;Rangeview is on a mission to build the foundry system that reindustrializes America. We exist to break the legacy manufacturing trap by reinventing critical production for the twenty-first century. Through advanced software, deep automation, breakthroughs in materials science, and modern financing strategies, Rangeview rewrites both the cost curve and the power structure of making metal parts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;473&quot; data-end=&quot;484&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What’s in it for you&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;486&quot; data-end=&quot;813&quot;&gt;As a Full-Stack Software Engineer, you will help build the software layer that powers Rangeview’s modern factory operations. This role will focus on developing the FactoryOS application that connects production workflows, equipment telemetry, part tracking, quality traceability, and real-time manufacturing decision-making.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;815&quot; data-end=&quot;1098&quot;&gt;This is a high-ownership engineering role for someone who wants to build software close to the physical world. You will work across frontend, backend, databases, manufacturing systems, and industrial integrations to help turn factory operations into a modern, software-driven system.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;1100&quot; data-end=&quot;1264&quot;&gt;We are currently hiring for a full-stack generalist who can operate across the product stack and work closely with engineering, manufacturing, and operations teams. &amp;nbsp;You&#39;ll join as one of the earliest software engineers at Rangeview, helping establish technical patterns, shape the evolution of FactoryOS, and influence how software powers the next generation of American manufacturing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;1100&quot; data-end=&quot;1264&quot;&gt;This position’s internal job code is Software Engineer. We are currently hiring for Level 1 or 2.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;1266&quot; data-end=&quot;1286&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1288&quot; data-end=&quot;1367&quot;&gt;Design and develop production applications used daily by factory operators, engineers, and manufacturing teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1288&quot; data-end=&quot;1367&quot;&gt;Design and implement backend services, data models, and APIs for FactoryOS&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1288&quot; data-end=&quot;1367&quot;&gt;Integrate with factory equipment, sensors, and telemetry sources to give real-time visibility into production, part status, and quality data&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1288&quot; data-end=&quot;1367&quot;&gt;Partner with manufacturing, operations, and automation teams to identify pain points and ship practical tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li data-start=&quot;1288&quot; data-end=&quot;1367&quot;&gt;Help set technical patterns and engineering standards as an early member of the software team&lt;/li&gt

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Industrial Maintenance Technician&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compensation:&lt;/strong&gt; $28 – $42 hourly / $58,240 – $87,360 annually + equity&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; El Segundo, CA&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Work Policy:&lt;/strong&gt; Onsite&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Environment:&lt;/strong&gt; Lean manufacturing / factory buildout&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Core KPIs:&lt;/strong&gt; Production uptime, preventive maintenance execution, and fast issue resolution&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who we are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rangeview is on a mission to build the foundry system that reindustrializes America. We exist to break the legacy manufacturing trap by reinventing critical production for the twenty-first century. Through advanced software, deep automation, breakthroughs in materials science, and modern financing strategies, Rangeview rewrites both the cost curve and the power structure of making metal parts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What’s in it for you&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a hands-on opportunity to support the buildout and operation of a modern aerospace manufacturing factory. You will work across facility systems, industrial equipment, utilities, production infrastructure, and factory support needs that directly impact uptime and daily execution.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is a strong fit for someone who likes practical troubleshooting, fast issue resolution, and owning real infrastructure and equipment problems rather than simply processing work orders. As new equipment, systems, and production capacity come online, you will have the opportunity to grow with the factory and help shape how maintenance is executed in a lean, high-ownership environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute routine inspections and maintenance on facility systems, including HVAC, compressed air, plumbing, electrical distribution, utilities, and general facility infrastructure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Troubleshoot and repair industrial manufacturing equipment, automated machinery, and facility infrastructure to minimize operational downtime.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with installation of new production equipment, workstations, utility connections, and factory infrastructure as Rangeview scales.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Document maintenance activities, repairs, inspections, and equipment issues to support accurate recordkeeping.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain facility-wide safety standards, including emergency lighting, eyewash stations, first aid kits, and similar safety-related systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify recurring equipment problems and recommend practical improvements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with engineering, production, leadership, vendors, and contractors to support equipment uptime and facility readiness.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support preventive maintenance execution and help improve maintenance processes as the factory grows.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll need&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to diagnose and repair mechanical, electrical, and pneumatic systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience supporting facility systems such as HVAC, compressed air, plumbing, utilities, or electrical distribution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to read and interpret electrical schematics, floor plans, mechanical drawings, technical manuals, and equipment documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong troubleshooting skills with hands-on experience using hand tools and power tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to communicate technical facility or equipment issues clearly with engineering, production, leadership, and outside vendors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with Lockout/Tagout and general industrial safety protocols.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Must be able to work full-time, W2, onsite in El Segundo, CA.&lt;/li&

